						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. III) set up in the Basavēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Siṁgaṇa II A.D. 1219.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated on the full moon day, coupled with Monday of the Pramāthi, Āshāḍha Paurṇimā, Monday, one of the years of Singhaṇa. The date is irregular. The given <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> ended, not on a Monday, but on Saturday, 29th June, A.D. 1219.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of two warriors Mācha and Gōma in a cattle-raid at Abbalūru, led by Īśvaradēva of Beḷagavatti when the feudatory Siṅghaṇadēva was governing Banavāsi-12000.</p>						

						<p>Published in Ep. Ind, Vol. V, pp. 261 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
